    "title": "Optionally sweep funds, with certain wallet events",
    "body": "For certain events, it would increase user security to generate a transaction that sweeps funds into new keys.\n\nExamples when a sweep would be useful:\n- When importing a private key, such as a casascius coin or scratch-off.\n- When encrypting a previously-unencrypted wallet, and some coins remain on the unencrypted keys.\n\nThis sweep must be optional, in case the user has a reason to _not_ generate a transaction at that moment.\n",
